### Repro Steps & Context

Run the following code
```
var repo = Repository.Factory.GetCoreV2(source);
var packageSearchResource = await repo.GetResourceAsync<PackageSearchResource>();
CancellationToken cancellationTokenSearch = new CancellationTokenSource(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5.0)).Token;
var results = await packageSearchResource.SearchAsync("MyPackage", 
                        null, 0, 1, NullLogger.Instance,
                        cancellationTokenSearch);
```
it will run forever.

However the following code will execute correctly:
```
var repo = Repository.Factory.GetCoreV2(source);
var packageSearchResource = await repo.GetResourceAsync<PackageSearchResource>();
CancellationToken cancellationTokenSearch = new CancellationTokenSource(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5.0)).Token;
var results = await packageSearchResource.SearchAsync("MyPackage", 
                        new SearchFilter(false), 0, 1, NullLogger.Instance,
                        cancellationTokenSearch);
```

Even though the first code is false I would expect an error instead of running forever.

